<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="338" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1158,1545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1339,1365]" pageId="6" pageNumber="338">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[352,410,1339,1365]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="338">India</collectingCountry>
the species has been reported solely by 
<bibRefCitation author="Annandale, N." box="[857,1063,1339,1365]" pageId="6" pageNumber="338" pagination="35 - 43" refId="ref11442" refString="Annandale, N. (1907) The fauna of brackish water ponds at Port Canning, lower Bengal. Records of the Indian Museum, 1, 35 - 43." type="journal article" year="1907">Annandale (1907)</bibRefCitation>
. At this regard, the author writes: 
<emphasis box="[151,350,1374,1401]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="338">
“In 
<date box="[196,350,1374,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="338" value="1906-01">January 1906</date>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="338">
<taxonomicName box="[362,426,1375,1401]" genus="I" pageId="6" pageNumber="338" rank="species" species="took">I took</taxonomicName>
among filamentous algae from the ponds a representative of the Gastrotricha which agrees very closely with Zelinka’s (II) figure and description of
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Metschnikoff" authorityYear="1865" box="[784,1031,1411,1437]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Chaetonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="6" pageNumber="338" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="schultzei">Chaetonotus schultzei</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="338">which I have also seen in a similar situation in freshwater tanks in Calcutta and Chota Nagpur</emphasis>
”. It seems evident that such an identification, without any reference to the morphometry of the species, appears to be not scientifically appropriate. Consequently, this species should not be included among the 
<collectingCountry box="[625,683,1519,1545]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="338">India</collectingCountry>
fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
